<br>
I have two opal encrusted steins, the +25 cha ones, that I use to help with prices when I shop. I also wear Netted Kelp Gloves that I take off since they have a negative cha on them. After this I end up with a 110 cha and I see a definate change in price.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I finally had the pp to buy the ruby that I needed for my Shovel of Ponz as well as a few copies of Transcendence (making everfount for others) and Dimension (still need the water pet). So I headed to Freeport to buy the ruby first. I opened my trade screen with Jade, the merchant in NFP, and noticed that I had equipped my stiens nor took off my gloves. So for some reason I had clicked on my netted kelp gloves and went to click done, but I managed to receive 12pp for my gloves instead. I /petitioned of course and the GM told me to get over it and press on.<br>
<br>
So then I picked up my head, and headed to Sol Ro to get my shovel. I handed in the four parts and in return I received my Shovel of Ponz, the shovel from Najena, A Ruby, and A Gargoyle Eye. Obviously someone had brought the incorrect toes with them earlier and did not get the other three items back. So that was a good thing for me I suppose. <br>
<br>
Off to OOT now..I am sitting on the dock fishing away. I am using the +3% tinkered bait that I made and the +2% fishing pole that I looted from the forehead in Toxx. I get a message that says You have got better at fishing (123). Immediatly following that message it said, your fishing pole has broke. <br>
<br>
I get to OOT and get a copy of the 20 fire and water pet and I manage to sucessfully research both 24 pets. So I get my water pet and I will give the fire to someone else someday. I gate back to NFP and flip jade off a few times, throw some taunting words at her and she still wont give me my gloves. I spend the last of my money buying her fire beetle eyes, cloth shirts and pants hoping the gloves will come up. My friend also dumps 250pp into her trying to help. Ended up getting to her Fine Steel weapon collection and she wanted almost 80pp for each one. So we quit there. <br>
<br>
I decided that I better log out now before anything else goes wrong. As I sit down I remember that I had placed my Treant staff in a summoned pouch a few minutes ago as I was shuffleling things about so I went to take it out so it would not poof, and would you guess that I could not open my flipping bags?! I had to log out and in to get it open...I took it out and immediatly camped after that...what a night...oh yea...and I had to camp when I was less than 1 blue from dinging as well. <p>Nukleus O`Chaos<BR>
